results.name: Expansion of psi(q) * phi(-q^18) * f(-q^6) / f(q^3)^3 in powers of q where phi(), psi(), f() are Ramanujan theta functions.
comment: Ramanujan theta functions: f(q) (see A121373), phi(q) (A000122), psi(q) (A010054), chi(q) (A000700).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
Michael Somos, Introduction to Ramanujan theta functions
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Ramanujan Theta Functions
formula: Expansion of eta(q^2)^2 * eta(q^3)^3 * eta(q^12)^3 * eta(q^18)^2 / (eta(q) * eta(q^6)^8 * eta(q^36)) in powers of q.
G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (36 t)) = f(t) where q = exp(2 Pi i t).
mathematica: eta[q_] := q^(1/24)*QPochhammer[q]; CoefficientList[Series[eta[q^2]^2 *eta[q^3]^3*eta[q^12]^3*eta[q^18]^2/(eta[q]*eta[q^6]^8*eta[q^36]), {q, 0, 50}], q] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Aug 08 2018 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x^2 + A)^2 * eta(x^3 + A)^3 * eta(x^12 + A)^3 * eta(x^18 + A)^2 / (eta(x + A) * eta(x^6 + A)^8 * eta(x^36 + A)), n))};
